txt.en: 'Ah... I remember you, Elvenking....'
'Come to claim your vengeance upon me at last? Take it then.'
'My time is ended... and my children have abandoned me.'
'Ungwet√°ri has called us to Her in the south... but I cannot make such a journey.'
Instance: Bane of the Elvenking
'My legs are weak beneath me, and my body is ravaged with illness.'
'Whether it is by your hand or not, my death comes soon.'
'Do what you wish, Elvenking. It matters not.'
<rgb=#FF0000>The ground shifts beneath your feet as Iphantemel's children attack!</rgb>
'Hold fast! More will soon be upon us!'
'Iphantemel must not escape us again! Bring them down!'
'Do you feel that?'
'They come! To arms!'
'Come, [placeholder]....'
'The air of this place is fouled with Iphantemel's blight. She cannot be far....'
'Iphantemel is called the Old Mother in the Common Tongue, but she cares not for her children. Many as they are....'
'Hold.'
'It was Iphantemel's unquenchable thirst for the sap of Greenwood the Great that first drew her hither, but it did not sate her.'
'It is safe to press on, but we must step carefully....'
'King Thranduil, we have found her!'
'In the mind of Iphantemel, the forest was to be hers to feast upon, and soon she and her children came to Caras Tilion.'
'Iphantemel dwells in a small cavern ahead, but she has sent none of her children against us.'
'My kin and I repelled the broods of Iphantemel for five years, but such a defence could not hold.'
'I do not understand it!'
'When at last Legolas discovered the caves that would become Felegoth, I knew the time had come.'
'Iphantemel and her children overran the slopes beneath Caras Tilion, and I commanded my people to flee to our new fastness.'
'At once, Iphantemel was upon me! As the battle wore on, I was stung, but I dealt her a grievous wound before my retreat.'
<rgb=#FF0000>A bubbling hiss rises through the air, and at once, Iphantemel's children cease their attack!'</rgb>
'Alas, it was not enough....'
'Many did not live to see the splendour of Felegoth, but those that survived shall never forget the fall of Caras Tilion.'
'Long has she eluded us, but Iphantemel's evil will be ended at last this day.'
'We have arrived unharmed. Has Iphantemel revealed herself?'
'It is not far now. Let us hasten our pace!'
'[placeholder], to me!'
'I do not trust this respite, [placeholder], but the time has come to seek Iphantemel.'
'Let us go.'
'Tread carefully, Iphantemel's webs grow thicker....'
'What has become of you, Iphantemel? Why have you allowed me to come forth?'
'You were once a great foe of my people, Iphantemel, so consider this the only mercy I offer.'
'It is over at last....'
